        "kind": "pull_request",
        "title": "feat(incus): add incus direct provider",
        "body": "## Summary\n\nAdds a first-class `incus` provider to Crabbox for self-hosted Linux runners on Incus-managed infrastructure.\n\nCloses #249\n\n## What this does\n\n- New `internal/providers/incus` package implementing `SSHLeaseBackend`\n- Supports both containers and VMs with `--incus-instance-type container|vm`\n- Connects via the official Incus Go client using local Incus client config (TLS, OIDC, or unix socket)\n- Direct SSH lease lifecycle: acquire, resolve, list, release, touch, cleanup, doctor\n- Cloud-init bootstrap with per-lease SSH key injection\n- Optional TCP proxy device for published SSH port (`--incus-proxy-listen-port`)\n- Full config surface: YAML, environment variables, and CLI flags\n- Provider docs at `docs/providers/incus.md`\n\n## Security hardening (from autoreview)\n\n- OIDC tokens are not loaded when `--incus-insecure-tls` is set (prevents credential leakage to MITM endpoints)\n- Proxy listen host defaults to `127.0.0.1` instead of `0.0.0.0` (avoids exposing SSH on all interfaces)\n- VM proxy devices use `nat=true` as required by Incus\n- Address mode tolerates broken local Incus configs when explicit cert/insecure TLS is already provided\n\n## Correctness fixes (from autoreview)\n\n- Unqualified image aliases resolve against the local Incus daemon by default; `incus.remoteImageServer` is opt-in only\n- Invalid `--incus-instance-type` values are rejected instead of silently coercing to container\n- `local:` image alias prefix is stripped for unix-socket remotes\n- `applyDefaults` preserves explicit `SSHPort`/`CRABBOX_SSH_PORT` instead of always overwriting\n- Named Incus remotes inherit their configured project instead of always overriding to `default`\n- Resolve uses saved `ssh_user` and `ssh_port` from instance labels\n- Resolve falls back to configured SSH key when stored per-lease key is missing\n- `connectionArgsForAddress` searches all remotes for address matches\n- Custom acquire retry loop cleans up retained instances and keys on `keep=true` bootstrap retries\n- Doctor reports `mode=socket` and `auth=unix_socket` for local unix-socket remotes\n\n## Verification\n\n```\ngo vet ./...\ngo test -race ./...\n```\n\nAll tests pass with the race detector enabled. The incus provider package has 60+ unit tests covering registration, flags, acquire, resolve, list, release, touch, cleanup, doctor, image source resolution, SSH target construction, connection args, and bootstrap retry behavior.\n\n## Dependency review\n\n- Added `github.com/lxc/incus/v7 v7.1.0` for the official Incus Go client used by the new direct provider.\n- Reviewed the Socket obfuscated-code warning locally against the cached `v7.1.0` module contents. The shipped module contents are Go source, documentation, translations under `po/`, images, and generated API/schema files. I did not find bundled minified JavaScript, WASM, or opaque executable payloads in the released module.\n- Current assessment: likely false positive on non-Go assets, but maintainer acceptance is still requested because this is a new infrastructure SDK and built-in provider surface.\n\n## Live Incus proof\n\nRedacted live proof is in the PR discussion and covers:\n- `doctor`\n- delete-on-release `warmup -> run -> delete`\n- retained `warmup -> run -> stop -> reuse -> delete`\n",
